Description: Historical, cultural & unique bus excursions domestically & internationally characterize Step On Bus Tours.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Detroit Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: You have a lot going for you when you go on a Step On Bus Tour -- history, mystery, fun and laughs plus entertainment and information to make you a knowledgeable traveler!  I'm Rose Szwed --dedicated to making your time aboard a Step on Bus a fact-filled, fun-filled, unforgettable memory. I know my stuff because I spend the time researching at libraries & traveling to destinations so I know what is around every corner.... and how many steps from here to there & cool stuff you'll see in between. Examples? Take one of the favorites of our many popular tours, our excursion into the world of Amish traditions and culture -- the simple yet delicious farm dining and a horse-and-carriage way of life in a time that's not quite gone -- but it changes constantly. Or can go back to the long-gone times of Prohibition, to the River of Rum, as illegal booze came onto our shores, and into speakeasies throughout the Midwest -- and sometimes in a hail of bullets -- and where you can actually visit a legal speakeasy, still in existence today.  My background as a copy writer and Director of Public Relations has certainly helped tell accurate and fascinating stories. Though no Cecile D. DeMille, my cheesy DVDs help tell the rest of the story. Plus, I'm addicted to historic sites, juxtaposing new and old buildings, and tossing in a reenactor to tell the rest of the story.  And of course, I can't do all this fun stuff alone, there are the knowledgeable tour planners, the cracker jack designer, the copywriter who edited the Bible along with food and refreshment planners to provide snacks and beverages en route; entertainment people who provide fun and games, with prizes to help you enjoy yourself all the way there and back; plus careful, courteous and friendly drivers to make the miles go by safely and comfortably. So come on. Let's chat. Toss me an idea or two and watch what I can do with it. Step aboard a Step On Bus tour. It's the only way to go!

With our local presence throughout the entire State of Florida, our team is, hands down, the most qualified and efficient restoration company that you’ll find. We know the city like the back of our hands, and can have a team en route to your home or business within mere minutes. Water damage, regardless of the source (roof leak, water pipes, flood basement, sewer back up), can be a real pain to handle. If a cleanup is not attempted promptly, it can cause mold to grow; creating a plethora of health concerns. Don't wait until this happens, just call us now! With over a decade of experience, we know how to handle each and every situation; from just a small area, to an entire property, we will thoroughly inspect the place, advise you the best course of action, and even prepare a FREE estimate for you. We will take care of the affected area effectively, whilst protecting the rest of your property. We follow all IICRC and EPA regulations and recommendations, so you know that we’re reliable. At Water Damage North Miami Beach we understand completely, that quick response is the essential key in preventing further damage, and even reducing your cleanup costs. Ten years of professional and personalized service has led to our expertise within the industry.  Our main commitment is to minimize structural water damage to all properties we deal with. Our specialist water damage experts extract all water, dry, and dehumidify; they then apply deodorizer and disinfectant to the areas which have been flooded or damaged by water. Description: Careers Unlimited, Tyler is a school in Tyler.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Whether you’re a college student deciding on a major, a young professional beginning a career in your early 20s, or an adult needing a career change, the Careers Unlimited School in Tyler, Texas, can help. The goal of Career Unlimited is to provide exceptional, personalized career service to every one of its clients through its career testing, career advising, and career coaching programs. Career testing is for students and adults who aren’t sure of what profession they want. The testing is comprised of three sessions that measure interest in occupations, academic areas, and work and leisure activities, designed to identify how strongly a person feels using particular skills. After the sessions, members of the career testing department go over results with you and create a list of careers for you to consider. If you know what career you want to enter into and need assistance in job preparation, the center’s career coaching program is for you. The sessions are designed to introduce and refine strong skills in interviewing by highlighting your strengths, researching the company, maintaining some control in the interview, and more. The program offers four packages each with their own unique focus:   * Targeted Interview Preparation   * Targeted Interview Preparation and Practice   * Targeted Interview Preparation and Videotaped Practice   * Videotaped Practice Contact Careers Unlimited today for more information on admissions requirements or financial aid.
